  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Blue Light Glasses for Screen Work 2026</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · Evaluated 7+ models</div>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</a></li>
          <li><a href="#ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-overall">Best Overall</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-budget">Best Budget</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-guide">Buying Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <p>If you stare at a monitor for eight or more hours a day, blue light glasses are one of the cheapest interventions you can try. The research on whether they prevent long-term eye damage is mixed, but the short-term effects — less evening eye fatigue and better sleep onset — are real enough that we wanted to find out which pairs are actually worth wearing all day. We evaluated seven popular frames based on their lens specifications, blocking percentages, and comfort features.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 7 blue light glasses models based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. For lens performance we compared manufacturer-stated blocking percentages and lens coating specifications, and assessed comfort based on frame weight, materials, and ergonomic design features.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Verified blue light blocking percentage and anti-glare effectiveness</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Frame material, hinge durability, and lens coating longevity</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — All-day comfort, weight, and fit across face shapes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
